The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     IN THE CITY
                  
	 United SC striker Murithala Ali has been slapped with a Rs.30,000 fine by the IFA for being involved in a scuffle during which he had allegedly bitten a player belonging to the Calcutta Port Trust.          
	 Newly appointed Bengal coach Utpal Chatterjee had a meeting with his players on Saturday following which it has been learnt that team practice sessions will be held thrice weekly in the afternoons.          
	 The ONGC Bengal Premier League will conclude on Sunday with the Rungta Group meeting Stag International in the final at the Sukanta Sadan in Barrackpore. The Rungta group beat East Bengal in the semi-final          
	 The Army A and B sides won their respective matches against Armenian SC and Bombay Gymkhana respectively in the 75th All India and South Asia Rugby Tournament at the SAI and CCFC grounds on Saturday. Tamil Nadu Police lost to Bangalore. The Army are the defending champions.           
	 The 10th Kaviguru rally organised by the Bengal Motor Sports Club will be held on Saturday. The awards ceremony is on September 15. This rally had been postponed earlier.                 
